ArcSign — Malicious Address Blocklist Attribution
=================================================

The file `malicious_spenders.txt` in this directory is a merged, de-duplicated,
lowercased list of known malicious / phishing / exploited addresses, used by the
Token Approvals security view to flag dangerous spenders.

It is built ONLY from MIT-licensed sources (deliberately avoiding GPL-licensed
datasets such as ScamSniffer, which cannot be vendored into this Apache-2.0
repository). Each source below is MIT-licensed, permitting redistribution with
attribution.

Sources
-------

1. MyEtherWallet / ethereum-lists  (MIT)
   https://github.com/MyEtherWallet/ethereum-lists
   File: src/addresses/addresses-darklist.json
   Content used: the `address` field of each entry (phishing / scam addresses).

2. Revoke.cash / approval-exploit-list  (MIT)
   https://github.com/RevokeCash/approval-exploit-list
   Files: exploits/*.json (referenced by index.json)
   Content used: the `address` field of each entry under `addresses`
   (contracts involved in approval-exploit incidents).

